@@aFirst Crab Burrow@@N~
In First Crab Burrow, practical survival and legal formality occupy the same narrow ground.  Fog can condense in minutes and reduce the coast to a band of sound.  Old cairn posts stand beside harbor signs that frame passage in different terms.  Anchor stones and sailcloth scraps mark maritime work pushed inland.  Routes branch east, south, west, and up, making this location a genuine tactical choice.  The sea is close enough to smell and hear, yet still distant enough to misjudge.


