ratio wall~
The ratio wall is carved with paired scripts, inland tally glyphs on one side and harbor load symbols on the other. Each horizontal band records one conversion family, with witness notches proving which formula was recognized in a given era. Scholars still debate the scratched-out band near eye level, where two jurisdictions once issued contradictory rates.
